f=poster.html?user=51161><span id= >Sehtlobo</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>4 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Apr 27th 12:19 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hello all, names's Sehtlobo. Proly a few of ya'll heard of me from Drinal. I am a lvl 22 Bard. Bein a bard is a great adventure, and I have to say bards get the best of every class out there! When starting a bard, it may seem a bit slow, weak, and discouraging. DON'T FALL INTO THE DOLDRUMS!! Bards are great, the most versitile of all. At Lvl 5, we get equivilant to SoW, 6 low lvl heal (great w/ lute), lvl 8 Crowd control Lull, 12 DD, 16 underwater song (people love this @ Rathe & Oasis), 17 Dual Wield (wohoo) and sneak (wohoo again), 19 Invisible (great for getting into hard areas, but make sure you tell castors w/ pets, CAUSE THEY [the pets] DISAPEARE WHEN U DO THIS. I have gotten many pissed by accident). What is also nice about the invisi song, is that if you play the role of a bards' bard (polite, unselfish, always willing to group), people will help you get the items you need in areas if you are a bit low on the level, and invisible helps you move around w/o bein killed. Lvl 20, MANA SONG (the most addictive to all castors in game [nicknamed "crack" by many of my friends] ), and binding song, which helps groups a great deal by slowing attack time tremendously. 21, eh, the teleport song, good for novelty, but great in places like Kelethin, Aviak, and other platform areas for getting down in a hurry (just have flute on standby, bad part). Lvl 22, dis-enchant song, good for pesky enchants by those shamans, oracles, embalmers, and other baddies. That's what I have reached so far. I've also managed to attain the WHOLE lambent armor class, by going to each area w/ the components, and helping/buffing/healing/ and "cracking" higher lvl chars. Thanks to all those people, BTW. Only catch is the the cost of the gems for the armor, but FAR worth it in the end. Weapons, well, there are many to choose. Keep all of your weapon abilities (1hb, 1hs, pierce, & h2h) up to par. I didn't do this with my 1hs, but I found best way to catch up is with Thulian Blade Claws. Just go to a little easier area, and slash away for a little. Also, LEARN TO BIND YOURSELF. Very important, as you can sing healing song w/ lute, and bind wounds to heal 10x faster than you would normally. Oh, also, make a point to get the Deception Mask. Nice ac, GREAT charisma, and let's you go to ANY city in Norath, making out of the way trips for food, equip, or selling junk not such a hastle, specially when near Ogguk, Neriak, or Grobb. Well, can't wait to further venture into troubadorian customs. If you have any questions, my new bardish friends, email me. I will answer ALL I know. Be well, hunt well, sing on.<br>-Seht<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
