<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98840487639140></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98840487639140><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=98840487639140>RE: Being A Bard</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=98840487639140#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=31993><span id=Scholar>Taamas</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>63 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Apr 27th 4:54 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.10]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>i would like to add to your great post, that i can't tell you how important it is to keep piercing skill up! we get AWESOME piercers at later lvls (ex. Sionachie's Partisan 9/19 int2 cha6 svmagic5 and Blade of Fiery Lamentations 5/18 proc: fingers of fire - 28dd starting at low 20s i think). so until you get a good piercer, use a bloodstained fang in offhand when meleeing (9/32 bought for under 100pp). they are also found off snow cougars in iceclad ocean (velious). you can solo them at around low 30s, or grp them.<br><br>Taamas Starsinger<br>36th Season<br>House of Wargoth<br>Saryrn<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
