	   <tr><td colspan=2>I went with CHA and AGI, I am glad i spent the points in AGI. If you don't know already our songs tend to piss things off, that extra AGI really helps. Bards don't have the HP's to be a full time tank, but if necessary i can stand in there for a while to help the tanks out. Often times I take much less damage than the tanks do because of my high AGI.<br><br>CHA is also important if you want to solo, I was able to solo froon and choon at lvl 27 (both red to me then) only loosing a bubble of health. CHA will also help with your mez spells, allowing&nbsp;&nbsp;you to fill in if there isn't an enchanter in the group.<br><br>In the end it all boils down to how you want to play your bard. Of all the stats for a bard the 3 most important are CHA, AGI, and DEX.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
