	   <tr><td colspan=2>ok i was doing crowd control and mana/defense songs for a grp in The Overthere tonight right. and when i charmed an add we had, i discovered something. after you charm your target, select the one all your other grp members are smoking up. then type this: /pet attack. that immediately sends your pet after that guy and thus helpin your grp. well i was thinkin bout that so i tried it on some more monsters in The Overthere. well i found out, you can get massive amounts of xp and pockets full of money if you use /pet attack command and not the "run up and let the other target hit you" method. ths way, you won't get hurt and you can watch charm more carefully. also it allows minimal time for you to answer those annoying tells when your kiting&nbsp;&nbsp;=)<br><br>this might sometimes save your life, especially HGs or cyclops that you should be charm kiting for MASSIVE amounts of money and loot for some quick lvling through hell  =)<br><br>BUT DON'T FORGET TO *ALWAYS* HAVE SELOS UP, NEVER EVER TRY KITING HGs OR CYCLOPS WITHOUT IT!<br><br>Taamas Starsinger<br>31st Season<br>House of Wargoth<br>Saryrn<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
